33:08.186 --> 33:09.988 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and president-elect Trump.

33:10.021 --> 33:14.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But first: a story about an
effort in Flint,
Michigan, to help its youngest
residents cope

33:14.860 --> 33:18.096 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with the possible effects of
lead-contaminated
water.

33:18.129 --> 33:22.634 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of our weekly series
on education,
Making the Grade.

33:22.667 --> 33:30.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: More than a
year after alarmingly
high levels of lead were found
in Flint's

33:30.308 --> 33:35.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
water supply, the city has
opened a free all-day
early childhood center for
children 2 months

33:35.981 --> 33:37.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to 5 years of age.

33:37.716 --> 33:39.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BOB BARNETT, University of
Michigan: It's
for any children currently
living in Flint

33:39.985 --> 33:45.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or were living in Flint when
lead exposure
was at its worst.

33:45.123 --> 33:50.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Bob Barnett, a
dean of education
for the University of Michigan
in Flint, helped

33:50.562 --> 33:52.397 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
create the new early learning
program.

33:52.430 --> 33:53.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BOB BARNETT: We made phone
calls.

33:53.999 --> 33:57.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We went door to door to every
single neighborhood
in the city.

33:57.168 --> 34:02.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Barnett had a
mission, to
reach families with the youngest
children.

34:02.540 --> 34:05.911 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
That's because lead is a
neurotoxin that targets
the developing brain.

34:05.944 --> 34:07.646 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

34:07.679 --> 34:09.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONA HANNA-ATTISHA, Hurley
Medical Center:
A child's brain doubles in size
from zero

34:10.015 --> 34:11.917 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to 2.

34:11.950 --> 34:18.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when you have these insults
to the developing
brain at such a young age, it
really impacts

34:18.623 --> 34:21.092 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that entire trajectory of
learning.

34:21.126 --> 34:26.798 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Mona
Hanna-Attisha, a pediatrician
who discovered elevated lead
levels in Flint's

34:26.831 --> 34:31.436 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
children, says there's a
well-established
link between lead exposure and
learning disabilities.

34:31.469 --> 34:33.238 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

34:33.271 --> 34:37.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONA HANNA-ATTISHA: Lead has
been shown to
drop children's I.Q., so it
impacts how they

34:37.108 --> 34:39.344 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
think, and it impacts how they
act.

34:39.377 --> 34:46.751 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It has been linked to
attention-deficit disorder,
impulsivity, many other
developmental delays.

34:46.785 --> 34:52.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And so it has these
life-course-altering
consequences.

34:52.257 --> 34:58.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: More than
5,000 of Flint's
youngest children were put in
danger when

34:58.063 --> 35:03.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the city switched to a new water
source, the
Flint River, in the spring of
2014, causing

35:03.234 --> 35:07.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lead from aging pipes to leach
into the system.

35:07.238 --> 35:11.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since then, Flint officials have
switched
back to Lake Huron for their
water supply,

35:11.710 --> 35:16.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and although lead levels have
been dramatically
reduced, residents are still
urged to use

35:16.948 --> 35:21.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bottled or filtered water for
everything from
drinking to bathing.

35:21.086 --> 35:27.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The lead exposure lasted only 18
months, but
health officials say a threat
still exists.

35:27.225 --> 35:29.094 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:29.127 --> 35:30.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONA HANNA-ATTISHA: Imagine
these little babies
who were on formula, and all
they're getting

35:30.962 --> 35:35.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is this lead-tainted water mixed
with powdered
formula for the entire year, not
that they're

35:35.533 --> 35:36.868 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
all going to have problems.

35:36.901 --> 35:38.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we're not going to wait to
see who is
going to have problems.

35:38.737 --> 35:41.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Hanna-Attisha
sees the new
child care facility as a needed
intervention.

35:41.973 --> 35:43.842 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:43.875 --> 35:46.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONA HANNA-ATTISHA: The most
important medication
that I can prescribe to our
Flint kids is

35:46.644 --> 35:47.612 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
early education.

35:47.645 --> 35:48.947 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People are like, you're a
doctor.

35:48.980 --> 35:50.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Don't you want like, you know,
health care
stuff?

35:50.181 --> 35:52.050 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm like, no, I want early
education.

35:52.083 --> 35:57.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The center is
an expansion
of a high-quality program called
Great Expectations

35:57.288 --> 36:00.458 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Early Childhood run by the
University of Michigan
in Flint.

36:00.492 --> 36:07.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BOB BARNETT: We know that lead
exposure, especially
in our youngest children, birth
to 5, affects

36:07.265 --> 36:09.768 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their cognition and their
behavior.

36:09.801 --> 36:15.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We also know that the impact of
early childhood
education and intervention can
counter that.

36:15.740 --> 36:20.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The free
program has been
able to accommodate 240
children.

36:20.278 --> 36:26.051 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Another 220 families remain on
the wait-list.

36:26.084 --> 36:30.555 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Major donations from 10
foundations, as well
as millions from the state of
Michigan, cover

36:30.588 --> 36:37.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tuition costs as high as $15,000
to $20,000
per child per year.

36:37.595 --> 36:41.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Joyce Sanders says she and her
husband could
not have afforded the program
for their 3-year-old

36:41.966 --> 36:46.504 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
daughter, Nyla (ph).

36:46.538 --> 36:49.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sanders is anxious to protect
her child's
ability to learn.

36:49.574 --> 36:52.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOYCE SANDERS, Mother: She's so
incredibly
bright.

36:52.911 --> 37:00.785 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's terrifying to think
that this exposure
could take that away from her.

37:00.819 --> 37:03.588 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is terrifying.

37:03.621 --> 37:08.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'm trying to do everything
I can to give
her the resources, so that she
can hold on

37:08.326 --> 37:10.061 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to that.

37:10.095 --> 37:13.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Nyla and her
5-year-old
sister, Kaia (ph), both tested
positive for

37:13.965 --> 37:16.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
low levels of lead in their
blood.

37:16.568 --> 37:22.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But because lead has a short
window of detection
in the bloodstream, Sanders is
unsure how

37:22.207 --> 37:23.541 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
much her children ingested.

37:23.575 --> 37:26.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOYCE SANDERS: I don't really
know what their
exposure level is.

37:26.177 --> 37:32.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every time they get anything,
I'm worried:
Is this something that I'm
missing?

37:32.217 --> 37:37.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Like many
parents in Flint,
the experience has left Sanders
feeling uneasy.

37:37.155 --> 37:43.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOYCE SANDERS: I have noticed
with my daughter
Nyla, she can sometimes get
upset, and it's

37:43.094 --> 37:45.063 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
very, very hard to calm her
down.

37:45.096 --> 37:49.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that just may be one of
those quirky things,
or it could mean something.

37:49.134 --> 37:51.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And if it means something,
that's huge.

37:51.302 --> 37:58.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so those type of things are
always in
the back of my mind.

37:58.276 --> 38:04.883 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Great
Expectations uses
the Reggio Emilia teaching
approach, which

38:04.916 --> 38:09.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
emphasizes emotional well-being,
something
educators believe is a good fit
for kids with

38:09.954 --> 38:11.723 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
possible lead exposure.

38:11.756 --> 38:13.591 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lead teacher Katie McCormack:

38:13.625 --> 38:16.060 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KATIE MCCORMACK, Great
Expectations: We're
working a lot with impulse
control, so everyone

38:16.094 --> 38:19.097 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can listen, everyone can take
turns and pay
attention.

38:19.130 --> 38:22.634 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We really want to just see where
they are
at developmentally.

38:22.667 --> 38:24.335 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

38:24.369 --> 38:27.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MONA HANNA-ATTISHA: These early
childhood
teachers are actually brain
builders.

38:27.338 --> 38:29.440 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're building these kids'
neural connections.

38:29.474 --> 38:35.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is unethical for us to sit
back and wait
and study these kids in five, 10
years, and

38:35.647 --> 38:37.682 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
say, oh, look at the impact of
lead exposure.

38:37.715 --> 38:39.784 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We must be proactive.

38:39.817 --> 38:41.653 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We must be preventative.

38:41.686 --> 38:45.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The new center
is housed
in one of Flint's shuttered
elementary schools.

38:45.390 --> 38:50.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The city's school enrollment has
declined
dramatically since the 1980s,
when car manufacturing

38:50.361 --> 38:52.630 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
jobs started disappearing.

38:52.664 --> 38:54.432 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Flint school's superintendent,
Bilal Tawwab.

38:54.465 --> 38:58.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BILAL TAWWAB, Superintendent,
Flint Community
School: Right now, we have only
5,000 kids

38:58.770 --> 39:00.638 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in Flint Community Schools.

39:00.672 --> 39:03.241 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
At one time, there was about
50,000 kids.

39:03.274 --> 39:06.477 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Actually, we have more closed
buildings than
open buildings.

39:06.511 --> 39:12.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: More than 40
percent of
Flint's residents live below the
poverty line.

39:12.750 --> 39:16.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Superintendent Tawwab says
using vacant
buildings for early education
coupled with

39:17.021 --> 39:19.891 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
good nutrition will better
prepare Flint's
children.

39:19.924 --> 39:26.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BILAL TAWWAB: I would like to
believe this
is just the start of some very,
very important

39:26.631 --> 39:28.399 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
work.

39:28.433 --> 39:30.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: But while
educators hope
to expand the program, there's
only enough

39:31.002 --> 39:35.940 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
money to serve 240 of the 5,000
to 6,000 children
in the city.

39:35.974 --> 39:39.711 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And even those slots are
operating on limited
three-years grants.

39:39.744 --> 39:42.447 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

39:42.480 --> 39:47.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we reported
earlier, Michigan's
attorney general filed criminal
charges against

39:47.919 --> 39:53.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
city officials in Flint for
operating that
city's water systems in an
unsafe manner.

39:53.157 --> 39:57.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, it turns out Flint is not
alone in having
a lead contamination problem.

39:57.929 --> 40:01.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two recent news investigation
find two startling
numbers.

40:01.966 --> 40:08.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A Reuters investigation of lead
levels in
blood found nearly 3,000 areas
in the country

40:08.940 --> 40:13.177 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with contamination levels higher
than those
in Flint.

40:13.211 --> 40:19.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And a USA Today report found
that some four
million Americans get water from
utilities

40:19.050 --> 40:23.154 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that do not meet federal safe
drinking water
standards.

40:23.187 --> 40:26.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Laura Ungar was a lead reporter
on the USA
Today investigation.

40:26.991 --> 40:28.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And she joins me now.

40:28.726 --> 40:30.662 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Laura Ungar, welcome to the
program.

40:30.695 --> 40:34.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You and your colleagues focused
on smaller
communities around the country.

40:34.799 --> 40:36.434 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Why?

40:36.467 --> 40:41.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LAURA UNGAR, USA Today: Well, we
wanted to
look at the problem beyond Flint
and look

40:41.072 --> 40:44.242 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to see just how big the scope
was.

40:44.275 --> 40:50.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, basically, we looked at
where the
problem was the worst, and we
found that,

40:50.782 --> 40:59.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in these small water systems,
which are generally
located in rural areas, small,
remote communities,

40:59.290 --> 41:02.160 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the problem was worse in those
communities.

41:02.193 --> 41:05.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And give us an
example of what
you found.

41:05.496 --> 41:09.634 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You got a number of families you
write about
in this series.

41:09.667 --> 41:12.103 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LAURA UNGAR: Yes.

41:12.136 --> 41:18.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For example, one family in
Ranger, Texas,
they have a situation where
their 2-year-old

41:18.543 --> 41:22.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
son has high levels of lead in
his blood.

41:22.814 --> 41:29.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they lived there for about a
year, almost
a year, before finding out from
a citywide

41:29.354 --> 41:36.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
letter that they had high lead
in their city,
in their city's water supply.

41:36.728 --> 41:44.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then they -- actually, their
tap was tested,
and they didn't find out the
results of that

41:44.102 --> 41:45.169 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from the city.

41:45.203 --> 41:47.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They found it out from me,
actually.

41:47.238 --> 41:51.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I told them the levels that were
found in
their own tap.

41:51.976 --> 41:56.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So -- and they were very upset
about that
situation, because, you know,
their son is

41:56.447 --> 42:03.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
2, and he's facing high lead,
which, as you
know, just causes all sorts of
problems with

42:03.421 --> 42:04.856 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
children.

42:04.889 --> 42:07.125 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, again, it
wasn't just
this one small community.

42:07.158 --> 42:09.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You found something like four
million Americans
affected.

42:09.961 --> 42:13.064 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LAURA UNGAR: Yes, it's more than
four million.

42:13.097 --> 42:23.374 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That four million is places
where -- or people
affected by places that either
tested improperly

42:23.408 --> 42:25.309 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or skipped tests.

42:25.343 --> 42:31.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are even more than that
when you talk
about where high lead has been
found and,

42:31.149 --> 42:33.217 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in some cases, has not been
fixed.

42:33.251 --> 42:34.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Why...

42:34.252 --> 42:35.219 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

42:35.253 --> 42:36.220 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Sorry.

42:36.254 --> 42:38.055 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Didn't mean to interrupt.

42:38.089 --> 42:42.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But why is it that some of these
smaller communities
don't have the stringent
regulations that

42:42.894 --> 42:45.763 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
larger population areas do?

42:45.797 --> 42:52.603 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LAURA UNGAR: What -- the
rationale that I
have heard for the difference in
the rules

42:52.637 --> 42:55.006 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is the resource difference.

42:55.039 --> 43:02.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a vastly different --
vastly different
resources between the large
water systems

43:02.213 --> 43:07.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in big cities and these small
water systems
which only serve a few thousand
people.

43:07.585 --> 43:13.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, some of them are run by
folks who
may have another full-time job.

43:13.591 --> 43:22.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We found one place where, for
example, a farmer/rancher
ran a water system in his spare
time.

43:22.567 --> 43:24.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he tried his best, but it's
part-time
thing.

43:24.969 --> 43:30.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's a much different
situation than
in a large water system, where
you might have

43:30.107 --> 43:36.848 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
very educated folks and large
staffs dealing
with water quality.

43:36.881 --> 43:38.216 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, finally, who
is responsible?

43:38.249 --> 43:42.987 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Environmental Protection
Agency, I know
you talked to them.

43:43.020 --> 43:43.988 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do they say?

43:44.021 --> 43:45.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How do they explain it?

43:45.189 --> 43:49.160 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LAURA UNGAR: They -- there's
layers of responsibility.

43:49.193 --> 43:51.062 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First of all, there's the
utility.

43:51.095 --> 43:55.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's the states that are
supposed to be
enforcing those federal safe
drinking water

43:55.533 --> 43:56.601 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
standards.

43:56.634 --> 44:00.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then, ultimately, the buck
stops at the
EPA.

44:00.037 --> 44:05.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The EPA does tell me that they
are focusing
on these small water systems,
that they do

44:05.176 --> 44:09.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hope to make improvements in
this area.

44:09.547 --> 44:14.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's a multifaceted problem,
and with
no easy answers at all.

44:14.619 --> 44:16.988 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, some
excellent reporting.

44:17.021 --> 44:18.923 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I know you are going to be
following up
on that.

44:18.956 --> 44:21.092 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Laura Ungar with USA Today,
thank you.

44:21.125 --> 44:25.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LAURA UNGAR: Thank you.

44:25.396 --> 44:36.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally tonight,
part two of
Jeffrey Brown's conversation
with Bruce Springsteen.

44:36.741 --> 44:41.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The working-class rock 'n' roll
hero talks
about his lifelong bouts of
depression, his

44:41.779 --> 44:44.916 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
love of reading, and the
election of Donald
Trump.

44:44.949 --> 44:50.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: On a visit with
Bruce Springsteen
at his home in rural New Jersey,
most of the

44:50.254 --> 44:54.792 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
talk, of course, was about
music, the core
of his life and career.

44:54.825 --> 45:00.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But part of the story he tells
about his rise
to the world stage also involved
books, what

45:00.398 --> 45:03.367 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he describes in his memoir as
his self-education.

45:03.401 --> 45:06.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN, Musician: I
think, when
I discovered the Russian guys,
they were -- that

45:06.237 --> 45:07.204 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
was...

45:07.238 --> 45:08.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The Russians did
it?

45:08.239 --> 45:09.206 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

45:09.240 --> 45:11.008 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: That was the
big thing.

45:11.042 --> 45:12.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You mean like the
big hitters,
like Dostoyevsky and Tolstoy and
those guys?

45:12.643 --> 45:14.545 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: The big
hitters, yes.

45:14.579 --> 45:18.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yes, when I got into "Anna
Karenina" and "Brothers
Karamazov" and "Crime and
Punishment," that

45:18.849 --> 45:22.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was the stuff that -- that had a
big effect
on me, because it was so
psychological.

45:22.420 --> 45:25.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Does your reading
affect your
writing as a songwriter?

45:25.156 --> 45:31.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: I think it
affects you
internally in a way that's not
immediately

45:31.829 --> 45:36.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
evident, but that it simply
increases your
frame of reference.

45:36.734 --> 45:44.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You learn more about the craft
of writing,
what good writing feels like.

45:44.308 --> 45:47.878 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But, mostly, it just enlarges
you as an individual.

45:47.912 --> 45:52.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The one thing I wished for my
children is
that they'd be readers.

45:52.249 --> 45:54.051 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
And...

45:54.085 --> 45:56.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, and are
they, because
that's what I was going to ask
you, because,

45:56.187 --> 45:57.154 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nowadays..

45:57.188 --> 45:58.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: No.

45:58.189 --> 45:59.156 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
No.

45:59.190 --> 46:00.157 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: They're not.

46:00.191 --> 46:01.959 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

46:01.993 --> 46:02.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Their father
didn't make himself
a reader until around 30, so the
kids, in

46:02.693 --> 46:09.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their 20s, still have time.

46:09.500 --> 46:13.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
By that point, Springsteen had
become a major
rock star.

46:14.005 --> 46:19.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, in his 30s, he also
suffered a serious
bout of depression, something he
would struggle

46:19.443 --> 46:25.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with throughout his life,
including an episode
as recently as his early 60s,
all while keeping

46:25.950 --> 46:29.020 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
up a rigorous touring and
recording career.

46:29.053 --> 46:35.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Springsteen, now 67, credits his
wife, Patti,
and years of counseling and
antidepressants

46:35.760 --> 46:37.561 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with getting him through.

46:37.595 --> 46:40.331 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He writes candidly of these
struggles in his
new memoir.

46:40.364 --> 46:44.435 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: It was a big
enough part
of my life to where it felt like
it needed

46:44.468 --> 46:46.837 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to be included in the book, you
know?

46:46.871 --> 46:54.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, also, I think it was an
insight into
some of your creative fire,
where it comes

46:54.745 --> 46:56.547 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
from.

46:56.580 --> 47:02.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I wrote -- the premise of the
book was to
give my audience an insight into
how I created,

47:02.153 --> 47:06.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and what were -- what's the fuel
for the fire.

47:06.157 --> 47:10.027 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You see them as
combined, twined.

47:10.061 --> 47:13.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a kind of trope of many
artists of
creativity and madness.

47:13.664 --> 47:18.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: Mental
illness and creativity
are -- it's a thin line in
between the two.

47:18.035 --> 47:20.438 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I tend to believe that.

47:20.471 --> 47:22.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know many artists who
are not crazy.

47:22.540 --> 47:26.277 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Most of the artists I know are
crazy in one
way or another.

47:26.310 --> 47:28.079 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think that's why you get into
it.

47:28.112 --> 47:32.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're in pursuit of a certain
sort of peace
that's very, very, very
difficult to come

47:32.850 --> 47:34.719 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by.

47:34.752 --> 47:45.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I realized the only time I
felt complete
and peaceful was while I was
playing or shortly

47:45.062 --> 47:55.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
afterwards, even though it was
in front of
thousands of other people, which
most people

47:55.139 --> 47:56.540 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wouldn't consider to be a safe
place.

47:56.574 --> 47:57.541 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
For me...

47:57.575 --> 47:58.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: No, they
wouldn't.

47:58.576 --> 47:59.543 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, why is that a safe place?

47:59.577 --> 48:01.378 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: For me, it's
always been.

48:01.412 --> 48:11.021 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For me, once I count the band
in, and I delve
deep into my song, I feel a
certain sort of

48:11.055 --> 48:17.795 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
integrity and integration that I
rarely find
in my daily life.

48:17.828 --> 48:22.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's better now than it used to
be, but it's
still something that, if I want
to deeply

48:22.800 --> 48:29.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
experience it, I walk on stage,
I play, I
perform, I create, I write.

48:29.173 --> 48:33.611 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's where sort of that
peace comes
over me.

48:33.644 --> 48:40.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: As he matured as
an artist,
Springsteen's music took on
issues of the

48:40.317 --> 48:49.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
political culture, Vietnam,
poverty, those
left behind in the 2008
recession.

48:49.360 --> 48:56.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: I integrated
it because
politics and life go hand in
hand.

48:56.367 --> 48:58.969 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so it needed to be a part of
my music.

48:59.003 --> 49:03.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Thus, the different social
forces that affected
my parents' lives or my friends'
lives or

49:03.374 --> 49:08.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I saw around me became essential
for me to
write about.

49:08.512 --> 49:13.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He also became
more up front
in his own politics, joining
Barack Obama

49:13.851 --> 49:18.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the campaign trail, and, in
the recent
election, supporting Hillary
Clinton.

49:18.489 --> 49:23.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: I was going
around the
world swearing -- I was betting
on Hillary,

49:23.160 --> 49:26.197 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
going around the world,
interview after interview.

49:26.230 --> 49:29.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And you were
wrong, like many
people.

49:29.300 --> 49:30.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: Yes.

49:30.301 --> 49:31.268 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

49:31.302 --> 49:32.236 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But what explains
it?

49:32.269 --> 49:34.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRUCE SPRINGSTEEN: I think a lot
of things.

49:34.071 --> 49:36.507 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think that people with
legitimate concerns
about how -- how are you going
to live, how

49:36.540 --> 49:40.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are you going to -- where are
you going to
find your jobs?

49:40.077 --> 49:46.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Deindustrialization that I have
written about
for 40 years left a good part of
the American

49:46.116 --> 49:47.318 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
public behind.

49:47.351 --> 49:50.788 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think if somebody comes up
and simply
says, your jobs?

49:50.821 --> 49:52.256 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm going to bring them back.

49:52.289 --> 49:54.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're not comfortable with the
browning of
America?

49:54.124 --> 49:55.759 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm going to build a wall.

49:55.793 --> 49:58.996 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ISIS, I'm going to defeat them.

49:59.029 --> 50:06.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those are very -- it's a simple,
but it was
a compelling message for a lot
of people.

50:06.136 --> 50:07.872 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
And...

50:07.905 --> 50:09.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But these are the
people that
you have been writing about for
all those

50:09.206 --> 50:10.174 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
